By Victor Adeoti  Osogbo  –  Osun has recorded 17 fresh coronavirus cases, bringing the total number of infections in the state to 263. Dr Rafiu Isamotu, the state’s Commissioner For Health, in a statement in Osogbo, said 11 patients were also discharged from isolation centre in the state after recovering from the disease. Isamotu said the new cases were contacts of the previous patients in the state. The Commissioner appealed to residents to always observe all the precautionary measures laid down against the spread of the virus. Isamotu said with the new cases, the number of confirmed cases in the state had risen to 263 with 135 active cases. He said the state had successfully treated and discharged 121 patients with seven deaths recorded so far. (NAN) By VIctor Adeoti Osogbo - The Osun government on Friday said it had recorded 22 new COVID-19 cases in the state, barely 24 hours after 17 cases were confirmed. Dr Rafiu Isamotu, the Commissioner for Health, in a statement in Osogbo, said that government might be forced to impose fresh… June 26, 2020 In "News" By Victor Adeoti Osogbo - The Osun Government says it has recorded 10 new cases of COVID-19, bringing the total number of infections in the state to 116. Dr Rafiu Isamotu, the State Commissioner for Health, said in Osogbo on Sunday that the new cases were from contact tracing of… June 28, 2020 In "Health" By Victor Adeoti Osogbo - Mr Wole Oyebamiji, the Secretary to Osun Government (SSG) has tested positive to COVID-19, bringing the total number of infections in the state to 127. Dr Rafiu Isamotu, the State Commissioner for Health Commissioner, who disclosed this in a statement in Osogbo on Tuesday, said… July 1, 2020 In "Health"